# Why the PipeModel?

The **PipeModel** is a deliberately idealized yet physically plausible
valley scenario. It distills terrain to the essentials (parabolic
cross-valley profile) and optional features (left-side hill, right-side
pond or hollow), so that dominant **microclimate drivers** become
visible and testable:

-   **Radiation** via terrain exposure `cos(i)` from slope & aspect
-   **Elevation**: daytime negative lapse; pre-dawn weak inversion
-   **Cold-air pooling** along the valley axis (Gaussian trough)
-   **Surface type / land-cover** (grass / forest / water / bare soil /
    maize) alters heating, shading, roughness and nocturnal behaviour

You can sample synthetic stations, train interpolators (IDW, Kriging
variants, RF, GAM), and assess them with **spatial LBO-CV**.

> ðŸ”§ This document keeps the previous behaviour but extends the physics
> with a modular **land-cover layer** that feeds into both daytime and
> night fields.

![](images/pipe.png)



# D. Physics & Scenario Builder â€” Cheat Sheet (enhanced LC model)

## D.1 Generated rasters & derived fields

| Name | Unit | What it is | How itâ€™s built |
|------------|-----------:|--------------|----------------------------------|
| `E` (`elev`) | m | Ground elevation | Parabolic â€œhalf-pipeâ€ across **y**; + optional hill; âˆ’ optional pond/hollow |
| `slp`, `asp` | rad | Slope, aspect | `terra::terrain(E, "slope"/"aspect", "radians")` |
| `I14`, `I05` | â€“ | Cosine solar incidence at 14/05 UTC | `cosi_fun(alt, az, slp, asp)`, clamped to `[0,1]` |
| `lc` | cat | Land-cover class | {Forest, Water, Bare Soil, Maize}; rules from hill/slope/water masks |
| `hillW` | 0â€“1 | Hill weight (1 inside footprint) | Disk/Gaussian on left third; combines main + optional micro-hills |
| `lake` | 0/1 | Water mask | 1 only when `lake_choice == "water"` (disk on right third) |
| `I14_eff` | â€“ | **Shaded** incidence (day) | `I14 * shade_fac_by_lc[lc]` |
| `Î±I(lc)` | â€“ | Daytime solar sensitivity by LC | Look-up from `alpha_I_by_lc` |
| `dawn_bias(lc)` | Â°C | Additive pre-dawn bias by LC | Look-up from `dawn_bias_by_lc` |
| `pool_fac(lc)` | â€“ | Pooling multiplier by LC | Look-up from `pool_fac_by_lc` |
| `R14` (`T14`) | Â°C | Daytime â€œtruthâ€ temperature field | Eq. (below) |
| `R05` (`T05`) | Â°C | Pre-dawn â€œtruthâ€ temperature field | Eq. (below) |

## D.2 Governing equations

Let \$\overline{E}\$ be the domain-mean elevation. Define the
cross-valley cold-pool kernel

$$
\texttt{pool\_base} \;=\; A \exp\!\left[-(d_y/w)^2\right],\quad d_y=|y-y_0|,
$$

blocked over the hill by `(1 âˆ’ pool_block_gain * hillW)`.

**Day (14 UTC)**

$$
T_{14} \;=\; T0_{14} \;+\; \texttt{lapse\_14}\,(E-\overline{E})
\;+\; \alpha_I(\texttt{lc})\, I_{14}^{\text{eff}}
\;+\; \varepsilon_{14},
\quad
I_{14}^{\text{eff}} = I_{14}\cdot \texttt{shade\_fac}(\texttt{lc}).
$$

**Pre-dawn (05 UTC)**

$$
T_{05} \;=\; T0_{05} \;+\; \texttt{inv\_05}\,(E-\overline{E})
\;+\; \eta_{\text{slope}}\;\texttt{slp}
\;-\; \texttt{pool\_base}\cdot(1-\texttt{pool\_block\_gain}\cdot\texttt{hillW})\cdot \texttt{pool\_fac}(\texttt{lc})
\;+\; \texttt{dawn\_bias}(\texttt{lc})
\;+\; \varepsilon_{05}.
$$

Noise \$\varepsilon\_{14},\varepsilon\_{05}
\sim \mathcal{N}(0,,0.3\^2)\$ i.i.d.

> **Note vs. predecessor:** the former `warm_bias_water_dawn * lake`
> term is now folded into `dawn_bias(lc)` (class â€œWaterâ€); daytime
> `Î±_map` became `Î±I(lc) * I14_eff` with explicit canopy shading.

## D.3 Dials

### Global scalars

| Parameter | Default | Sensible range | Affects | Visual signature (+) |
|-------------|------------:|------------:|-------------|--------------------|
| `T0_14` | 26.0 Â°C | 20â€“35 | T14 baseline | Uniform warming |
| `lapse_14` | âˆ’0.0065 Â°C/m | âˆ’0.01â€¦âˆ’0.002 | T14 vs elevation | Cooler rims, warmer floor |
| `T0_05` | 8.5 Â°C | 3â€“15 | T05 baseline | Uniform warming |
| `inv_05` | +0.003 Â°C/m | 0â€“0.008 | T05 vs elevation | Rims warmer vs floor |
| `Î·_slope` | 0.6 | 0â€“1.5 | T05 slope flow proxy | Steeper slopes a bit warmer at dawn |
| `pool_base` amplitude | 4.0 K | 1â€“8 | T05 pooling depth | Stronger blue band on valley axis |
| `w_pool` | 70 m | 40â€“150 | T05 pooling width | Narrower/broader cold band |
| `pool_block_gain` | 0.4 | 0â€“1 | Hill blocking | Warm â€œtongueâ€ over hill at dawn |
| `noise Ïƒ` | 0.3 K | 0â€“1 | Both | Fine speckle/random texture |

### Land-cover coefficients (by class)

Defaults used in the code:

| LC class | `alpha_I_by_lc` | `shade_fac_by_lc` | `dawn_bias_by_lc` (Â°C) | `pool_fac_by_lc` |
|--------------|-------------:|-------------:|---------------:|-------------:|
| Forest | 3.5 | 0.6 | +0.3 | 0.7 |
| Water | 1.5 | 1.0 | +1.2 | 0.8 |
| Bare Soil | 6.0 | 1.0 | âˆ’0.5 | 1.1 |
| Maize | 4.5 | 0.9 | +0.1 | 1.0 |

**Interpretation:** *Bare Soil* heats most by day and **enhances
pooling** (factor \> 1) and cool bias at dawn; *Forest* damps radiation
by day (shading) and **reduces pooling** (factor \< 1); *Water* heats
little by day, gets a **positive dawn bias** and reduced pooling;
*Maize* sits between grass and forest.

### Geometry/toggles

| Parameter | Default | Options / range | Effect |
|--------------|--------------|--------------|--------------------------------|
| `lake_choice` | `"water"` | `"none"`, `"water"`, `"hollow"` | Controls depression; only `"water"` sets LC=Water (thermal effects). |
| `hill_choice` | `"bump"` | `"none"`, `"bump"` | Adds blocking & relief. |
| `lake_diam_m` | 80 | 40â€“150 | Size of pond/hollow. |
| `lake_depth_m` | 10 | 5â€“30 | Depression depth. |
| `hill_diam_m` | 80 | 40â€“150 | Hill footprint. |
| `hill_height_m` | 50 | 10â€“120 | Hill relief. |
| `smooth_edges` | `FALSE` | bool | Soft pond rim if `TRUE`. |
| `hill_smooth` | `FALSE` | bool | Gaussian hill if `TRUE`. |
| *(optional)* micro-hills | off | `random_hills`, `micro_*` | Adds sub-footprint relief; included in `hillW`. |

## D.4 Quick â€œrecipesâ€

-   **Cloud/haze day** â†’ â†“ `alpha_I_by_lc` (all classes, esp.
    Bare/Maize) â†’ daytime LC contrasts fade; models lean on
    elevation/smoothness.
-   **Hotter afternoon** â†’ â†‘ `T0_14` (+1â€¦+3 K) â†’ uniform bias shift;
    rankings unchanged.
-   **Stronger pooling** â†’ â†‘ `pool_base` and/or â†“ `w_pool` â†’ sharper,
    deeper trough; drift-aware models gain.
-   **Water vs hollow** â†’ `"water"` sets LC=Water â†’ â†“ daytime heating, â†‘
    dawn warm bias, â†“ pooling; `"hollow"` keeps only geometry (no water
    thermals).
-   **Hill blocking** â†’ â†‘ `pool_block_gain` â†’ warm dawn tongue over
    hill; harder CV across blocks.
-   **Cover swaps** (what if): set a patch to *Bare Soil* â†’ warmer day,
    **colder dawn & stronger pooling**; to *Forest* â†’ cooler day,
    **weaker pooling & slight dawn warm-up**.

